  <Docs>
    <summary>Specifies the arguments used to customize a typeface, including variation axes and palette selection.</summary>
    <remarks><format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[
## Remarks

`SKFontArguments` is a ref struct that describes how to customize a <xref:SkiaSharp.SKTypeface>
when cloning it via <xref:SkiaSharp.SKTypeface.Clone(SkiaSharp.SKFontArguments)>. You can specify
which font collection index to use, the desired variation axis positions, which color palette to
apply, and any per-entry color overrides for that palette.

`SKFontArguments` is a ref struct and cannot be stored on the heap.

## Examples

```csharp
var coords = new SKFontVariationPositionCoordinate[]
{
    new SKFontVariationPositionCoordinate { Axis = SKFourByteTag.Parse("wght"), Value = 700 },
};
var args = new SKFontArguments
{
    VariationDesignPosition = coords,
    PaletteIndex = 0,
};
using var boldTypeface = typeface.Clone(args);
```
]]></format></remarks>
  </Docs>
